The paper deals with a communication problem involving multiple sources and broadcast channels, which is a typical problem in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves optimization techniques and combinatorial clustering, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of exchanging data over broadcast channels is also related to networked systems (cs.NI) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm that improves computational efficiency, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
